College: Sarvajanik College of Engineering and Technology, Surat
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
For the purpose of admission, a candidate shall have passed the Qualifying Examination with minimum eligibility criteria of percentage of marks in
(i) the Gujarat Board; or
(ii) the Central Board of Secondary Education
Provided that,
(a) the school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the State of Gujarat; or
(b) the school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the Union Territories of Daman and Diu or Dadra and Nagar Haveli and whose parents are of Gujarat origin; or
(iii) the Council of Indian School Certificate Examination, New Delhi:
Provided that,
(a) the school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the State of Gujarat; or
(b) the school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the Union Territories of Daman and Diu or Dadra and Nagar Haveli and whose parents are of Gujarat origin; or
(iv) the National Institute of Open Schooling:
Provided that,
(a) the study Center/school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the State of Gujarat; or
(b) the study Center/school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the Union Territories of Daman and Diu or Dadra and Nagar Haveli and whose parents are of Gujarat origin; or
(v) the International School Board:
Provided that,
(a) the study Center/school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the State of Gujarat; or
(b) the study Center/school in which the candidate has studied, shall have been located in the Union Territories of Daman and Diu or Dadra and Nagar Haveli and whose parents are of Gujarat origin; and
(vi) have appeared in JEE (Main) conducted in the corresponding academic year.
(2) A candidate whose parents are of Gujarat origin and are serving out of the Gujarat in the service of Central Government or other State Government, Armed Forces, Boards or Corporations owned or controlled by the Central Government or other State Government or any nationalized bank and who has passed the qualifying examination from the State where parents are serving and has appeared in the JEE (Main) conducted in the corresponding academic year, shall be eligible for admission and his candidature shall be included in the merit list prepared in accordance with the provisions of rule 11.
(3) A candidate who has passed the Qualifying Examination from any other State and,
(i) has appeared in JEE (Main) conducted in the corresponding academic year; and
(ii) whose parents are serving in the category of services as shown below and who are transferred from other States to Gujarat and have resumed their duties in the place where they are transferred in the state of Gujarat at the time of registration for admission, shall be eligible for admission and his candidature shall be included in the merit list prepared in accordance with the provision of Rule 11.

Eligiblity: The following is the criteria for the admission:70% Admissions are taken under Convener QuotaTo seek admission into the first year of a four-year b.tech course in any branch, he/she must satisfy the following requirements:A student must have passed the Intermediate Examination of the Board of Intermediate Education, Government of Telangana with Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry as optional subjects, or any other examination recognized by the Government of Telangana as its equivalent.All the eligible candidates for admission into First Year shall have to qualify in the EAMCET Examination conducted by the Govt. of Telangana. The candidates will be admitted by EAMCET Convener strictly in accordance with the rank secured at the Entrance Examination and keeping the rules applicable in view, regarding the reservation of seats of various categories of candidates.Management Quota:30% of the total seats will be considered under Management Quota.To seek admission under Management Quota, he/she must satisfy the following requirements.A student should either have obtained a rank or should have secured a minimum aggregate percentage of 50% in group subjects (Maths, Physics and Chemistry) in the Intermediate Examination of the Board of Intermediate Education, Government of Telangana or any other examination recognized by the Government of Telangana as its equivalent.30% of the total seats will be considered under Management Quota.Note: No reservation biased or any other concession will be given under Management Quota.Lateral Entry:Students of diploma stream are admitted at the second-year level of the bachelor degree programme.
Course_Detail: The department of Mechanical Engineering started in the year 2010 with an intake of 60 students. The department is well equipped with state of art laboratories and infrastructure in thrust areas. The basic workshop, computer aided engineering drawing, metallographic & material testing lab, mechanical measurements & metrology lab, machine shop, foundry and forging lab are well established. College: CMR Engineering College, Hyderabad
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity: A Bachelor’s degree in Engineering/Technology of Any Recognized University in the concerned discipline. Apart from requirements of qualifications as stated in the above, the admissions of sponsored candidates shall be taken. The number of Sponsored candidates shall not be more than two in each specialization and not more than five in each department.These seats are considered as supernumeraryHe / She must be the permanent employee with the sponsoring agency for at least (2) years, after obtaining the qualifying degree.The sponsoring agency must be a Government establishment or a public-sector undertaking, or a reputed private undertaking.The sponsoring agency shall certify that the candidates will be granted leave for pursuing the M.TECH. Full-Time course.The candidates should satisfy local/non-local status requirement as laid down in the Telangana Educational institutions (Regulation of Admissions) Order 1974 as amended from time to time.

College: Bharati Vidyapeeth’s College of Engineering for Women, Pune
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity: (1) Maharashtra State Candidature Candidate.-(i) The Candidate should be an Indian National;(ii) Passed HSC or its equivalent examination with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the Chemistry or Biotechnology or Biology or Technical or Vocational subjects, and obtained at least 50% marks (at least 45% marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) in the above subjects taken together; and obtained score in CET conducted by the Competent Authority.Or(ii) Passed Diploma in Engineering and Technology and obtained at least 50% marks (at least 45% marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only);Orii) Passed B.Sc. Degree from a Recognized University as defined by UGC and obtained at least 50% marks (at least 45% marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) and passed XII standard with Mathematics as a subject.(2) All India Candidature Candidates, Jammu and Kashmir Migrant Candidature Candidates.-(i) The Candidate should be an Indian National;(ii) Passed HSC or its equivalent examination with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the Chemistry or Biotechnology or Biology or Technical or Vocational subjects and obtained at least 50% marks (at least 45% marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) in the above subjects taken together and obtained score in JEE Main Paper I or in CET conducted by the Competent Authority;Or(ii) Passed Diploma in Engineering and Technology and obtained at least 50% marks (at least 45% marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only); Or ii) Passed B.Sc. Degree from a Recognized University as defined by University Grants Commission and obtained at least 50% marks (at least 45% marks, in case of Backward class categories and Persons with Disability candidates belonging to Maharashtra State only) and passed XII standard with Mathematics as a subject. (3) NRI / OCI / PIO, Children of Indian workers in the Gulf countries, Foreign National.- The candidate should have passed the HSC or its equivalent examination with Physics and Mathematics as compulsory subjects along with one of the Chemistry or Biotechnology or Biology or Technical or Vocational subjects, and obtained at least 50% marks in the above subjects taken together;

College: Sree Chitra Thirunal College of Engineering, Thiruvananthapuram
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity: A pass in the 12th standard examination of the Kerala State or examinations considered equivalent thereto with Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry as optional subjects with a separate minimum of 50% marks in Mathematics and overall 50% marks in Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry put together. OR Candidates who have passed Diploma in Engineering awarded by the State Board of Technical Education or Equivalent and must have a minimum of 60% marks. Relaxation of 5% marks will be allowed to SEBC candidates whose annual family income does not exceed 4.5Lakhs. For candidates belonging to SC/ST community, a pass in the qualifying examination will be sufficient. Note: Candidates belonging to socially and educationally backward classes as per G.O (P) 20^B6/Edn.dt.2- 5-66 and amendments thereof with a total annual family income up to 4.5Lakhs will have a relaxation of 5% marks. Scheduled caste and Scheduled Tribe candidates need only a pass in the qualifying examination. In the case of candidates selected on the basis of the marks in the qualifying examinations 50% marks in Mathematics (University stipulation) and 50% marks in Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry put together (A.I.C.T.E stipulation) is required. For diploma holders 60% marks in final diploma examination is required. The relaxation given above for candidates belonging S.E.B.C and S.T are applicable here also. This is applicable only in the case of nominees of Govt, of India and nominees to reciprocal quota seats of other states. The candidates should have appeared for the qualifying examination before appearing for the Common Entrance Examination. No rounding off of percentage marks to the nearest whole number is permitted. Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity: The candidate must have clearly passed intermediate examination of U.P. Board or 10+2 level examination or its equivalent from any recognized Board / University without grace in each compulsory subject i.e. Physics and Mathematics and one optional subject as chemistry / Bio-Technology / Biology / Technical Vocational subject securing minimum 45% (40% marks for SC/ST category candidates) in aggregate in required three subjects.   Through UPSEE 201885% of the total intake available in Institute in B.Tech. will be filled by the candidates who will be allotted seats through UPSEE 2018. The 85% seats are filled as under:75% seats to be filled by the candidates who have clearly passed the intermediate examination from U.P. Board or 10+2 level examination or its equivalent from any recognized board/university or whose parents are Domicile of UP.10% seats to be filled by candidates, who have passed the qualifying examination from an Institution located outside U.P. and whose parents are not domicile of U.P. on the basis of JEE-MAIN-2018 or THROUGH UPSEE.Through Direct Admission Under Management Quota15% of the total intake available will be filled by the institute as per the laid down norms of UPSEE 2018 and State Government.Vacant Seats After Counselling of UPSEE 2018The vacant seats after counselling of UPSEE 2018 shall be filled by the Institute as per the laid down norms of UPSEE 2018 and the State Government.Admission to Fee Waiver seats for Economically Weaker Meritorious Students.As per AICTE notification Fee Waiver seats for economically weaker meritorious candidates are also available in B.Tech. course. The fee waiver seats will be limited to the maximum of 5% of the sanctioned intake in the course and will be over and above of the sanctioned intake.  No tuition fee will be charged from such candidates admitted against such seats.  The economically weaker students must submit certificate no. 12 (Income Certificate) at the time of verification of documents in counselling.  These seats are allotted through UPSEE counselling.ADMISSION TO KASHMIRI MIGRANTS IN FIRST YEARDirect admission to Kashmiri Migrants in the first year in each institute is to be made as per the latest instructions of AICTE and orders from U.P. Govt. Such admissions will be over and above the sanctioned intake and normally limited up to one admission per Institute affiliated to Dr. APJ AKTU, Lucknow. The detailed information will be published in the month of May 2018 in various newspapers and University website http://www.aktu.ac.in. The candidates, opting for admission under this scheme, need not appear in UPSEE-2018.Modes of Admission and Eligibility Criteria for Admission to B.TECH IInd Year (Lateral Entry)Through UPSEE 201820% of the total sanctioned intake available in the Institute for different courses at the first-year level.Eligibility to Appear in UPSEE 2018 for Admission to the IInd year of B.Tech (Lateral Entry) Candidates who have passed ‘three years Engg Diploma from an Institution located in U.P. with minimum 45% marks (40% for SC/ST) or ‘whose parents (Father or Mother) are domicile of Uttar Pradesh’ and he/she has passed three years Engg Diploma with minimum 45% marks (40% for SC/ST) recognized by the Board of Technical Education, U.P. in any branch of Engineering (Except Agriculture Engineering, Pharmacy and Architecture) are eligible for admission to the Second year in any Branch of Engineering/Technology.Candidates who have passed ‘three years B.Sc. degree and Passed XII standard with Mathematics as one of the subject’ from any recognized University, securing minimum 45% marks (40% for SC/ST) in aggregate.

College: CMR Technical Campus, Hyderabad
Approval: (AICTE) All India Council of Technical Education
Eligiblity:
a. A Bachelor’s degree in Engineering/Technology of Any Recognized University in the concerned discipline.
b. AMIE/AMIETE or similar qualifications recognized by UPSC as equivalent to B.E./B.Tech.
c. Valid GATE Score obtained in the GATE Examination.
Apart from requirements of qualifications as stated in the above, the admissions of sponsored candidates shall be taken.
1. The number of Sponsored candidates shall not be more than two in each specialization and not more than five in each department.
2. These seats are considered as supernumerary
3. He / She must be permanent employee with the sponsoring agency for at least (2) years, after obtaining the qualifying degree.
4. The sponsoring agency must be a Government establishment or a public-sector undertaking, or a reputed private undertaking.
5. The sponsoring agency shall-certify that the candidates will be granted leave for pursuing the M.TECH Full-Time course.
6. The candidates should satisfy local/non-local status requirement as laid down in the AP Educational institutions (Regulation of Admissions) Order 1974 as amended from time to time.
Course_Detail: It is 2 year full time course with affiliation of Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Hyderabad and approved by AICTE.
